<br>
Movies aren't made to appease fans. They're made to make money.  This film wasn't made for Tolkien fans, it as made for a general audience.  If the Tolkien purists can shell out 1 billion dollars in ticket sales, I'm sure you guys can find someone to make a movie exactly as it occurs in the book.  Jackson can't simply do whatever he wants when he's working with the largest budget in film history.  Studio execs give him that budget, and pay him to do a job for them.  They don't pay him to be accurate, they pay him to make a great movie that millions will go see. The fact that the movies are so hugely successful AND they get good reviews, is a bonus.  <br>
<br>
I'd say about 95% of the people that saw this movie so far have been extremely content, and the movie has garnered a ton of critical acclaim.  I can't think of a single film maker who would do something different.<br>
<br>
